This paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically counting the number of interior disjoint empty convex polygons in a point set. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves combinatorial aspects, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper also uses some graph theory concepts, which makes cs.GT (Graph Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some mathematical analysis, which suggests cs.MS (Mathematical Software) as a possible sub-category.
